<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Create Test Hub</title>
    <%- include('../partials/design-system') %>
    <style>
        /* ============================================================
           CREATE TEST HUB — three-column builder cards + gradient bg
           ============================================================ */
        body {
            background:
                radial-gradient(circle at top left, rgba(255,255,255,0.15), transparent 30%),
                linear-gradient(135deg, var(--primary-500) 0%, var(--primary-700) 100%);
            color: #fff;
            padding: var(--space-lg) var(--space-md);
        }

        .hub-container { max-width: 1200px; margin: 0 auto; }

        .hub-back-link {
            display: inline-flex;
            align-items: center;
            gap: var(--space-sm);
            color: rgba(255,255,255,0.85);
            text-decoration: none;
            font-weight: 700;
            margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
            transition: color var(--transition-fast);
        }
        .hub-back-link:hover { color: #fff; text-decoration: none; }

        .hero { text-align: center; margin-bottom: var(--space-xl); }
        .hero h1 { font-size: 2.5rem; font-weight: 900; letter-spacing: -0.04em; margin-bottom: var(--space-sm); }
        .hero p { max-width: 720px; margin: 0 auto; line-height: 1.7; opacity: 0.9; }

        .builder-note {
            margin-top: var(--space-md);
            display: inline-flex;
            align-items: center;
            gap: 10px;
            padding: 10px 18px;
            border-radius: var(--radius-full);
            background: rgba(255,255,255,0.12);
            border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.16);
            font-weight: 700;
            font-size: 0.9rem;
        }

        .grid {
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr));
            gap: var(--space-lg);
        }

        .builder-card {
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: column;
            gap: var(--space-md);
            padding: var(--space-xl);
            border-radius: var(--radius-xl);
            background: var(--surface-glass);
            backdrop-filter: blur(18px);
            -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(18px);
            text-decoration: none;
            color: var(--text-primary);
            box-shadow: var(--shadow-lg);
            border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.2);
            transition: transform var(--transition-base), box-shadow var(--transition-base);
        }
        .builder-card:hover {
            transform: translateY(-8px);
            box-shadow: var(--shadow-xl);
            text-decoration: none;
            color: var(--text-primary);
        }

        .reading { border-top: 6px solid var(--info); }
        .listening { border-top: 6px solid var(--success); }
        .writing { border-top: 6px solid #f97316; }

        .builder-card .icon { font-size: 3rem; line-height: 1; }
        .builder-card h2 { font-size: 1.4rem; font-weight: 900; letter-spacing: -0.02em; }
        .builder-card p { color: var(--text-secondary); line-height: 1.6; font-size: 0.9rem; }

        .feature-list {
            display: grid;
            gap: var(--space-sm);
            padding: var(--space-md);
            border-radius: var(--radius-md);
            background: var(--gray-50);
            border: 1px solid var(--border);
            font-size: 0.85rem;
        }
        .feature-list div { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: var(--space-sm); font-weight: 700; color: var(--text-secondary); }

        .cta {
            margin-top: auto;
            display: inline-flex;
            align-items: center;
            justify-content: center;
            padding: 14px 18px;
            border-radius: var(--radius-full);
            font-weight: 800;
            font-size: 0.9rem;
            color: #fff;
            background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--primary-500), var(--primary-600));
            box-shadow: 0 8px 20px rgba(99, 102, 241, 0.3);
            transition: box-shadow var(--transition-base);
        }
        .builder-card:hover .cta { box-shadow: 0 12px 28px rgba(99, 102, 241, 0.4); }

        .footer-note {
            margin-top: var(--space-lg);
            padding: var(--space-md) var(--space-lg);
            border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
            background: rgba(255,255,255,0.1);
            border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.14);
            color: rgba(255,255,255,0.85);
            line-height: 1.7;
            font-size: 0.9rem;
        }

        body.dark-mode {
            background: radial-gradient(circle at top left, rgba(0,0,0,0.3), transparent 30%),
                        linear-gradient(135deg, #0f172a 0%, #1e293b 100%);
        }
        body.dark-mode .builder-card { background: var(--surface-glass); }
        body.dark-mode .feature-list { background: var(--gray-800); border-color: var(--border); }

        @media (max-width: 1080px) {
            .grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
            .hero h1 { font-size: 2rem; }
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="hub-container">
        <a href="/admin" class="hub-back-link">← Back to Admin Dashboard</a>

        <section class="hero">
            <h1>Builder-Based Test Creation</h1>
            <p>Each path below opens the real builder-style authoring interface. The platform save action is layered on top, so what you create here stays aligned with the exact reading, listening, and writing builders.</p>
            <div class="builder-note">Listening audio files are uploaded to the server and stored locally instead of embedding base64 inside the saved test.</div>
        </section>

        <section class="grid">
            <a href="/create-test-reading" class="builder-card reading">
                <div class="icon">📖</div>
                <div>
                    <h2>Reading Builder</h2>
                    <p>Use the full reading builder flow with the same tabs, passage layout, question generation tools, and export-matched renderer.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="feature-list">
                    <div>Builder-identical authoring shell</div>
                    <div>Reading passages and question blocks</div>
                    <div>Platform save routed into the builder page</div>
                </div>
                <div class="cta">Open Reading Builder</div>
            </a>

            <a href="/create-test-listening" class="builder-card listening">
                <div class="icon">🎧</div>
                <div>
                    <h2>Listening Builder</h2>
                    <p>Compose all four parts with the original listening builder interface while uploading audio files to the server.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="feature-list">
                    <div>Server-side audio storage</div>
                    <div>Part-by-part authoring with pause option</div>
                    <div>Student HTML keeps direct audio URLs</div>
                </div>
                <div class="cta">Open Listening Builder</div>
            </a>

            <a href="/create-test-writing" class="builder-card writing">
                <div class="icon">✍️</div>
                <div>
                    <h2>Writing Builder</h2>
                    <p>Author Task 1 and Task 2 in the original writing builder layout, including prompts, model answers, and the review workflow.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="feature-list">
                    <div>Task 1 and Task 2 builder parity</div>
                    <div>Review-ready student output</div>
                    <div>Platform save without losing builder styling</div>
                </div>
                <div class="cta">Open Writing Builder</div>
            </a>
        </section>

        <div class="footer-note">
            Saved tests render through the same shared exporter for student view, teacher preview, and HTML download, so the visual output stays consistent from authoring to delivery.
        </div>
    </div>
    <%- include('../partials/notifications') %>
</body>
</html>
